content: I've used this app for 7 years and it had been great. In October 2020 I started to get "new notifications" for old forum posts. I would get 40-50 notifications for very old forum posts. Very annoying and a waste of time. I'm very disappointed. I contacted support several times, but no solution in over three months.

Latest updates have completely broken the ability to view certain forums and post. Replicated this issue on several different forums and tested on WiFi and cellular connections. What's the point in this app?

I've got this app for the XDA forum, and as some other have noticed that XDA has been inaccessible using the Tapatalk app. Though the fault is on XDA side, since the users can't log in normally with the XDA app. Now the XDA app is finally back online and has a complete UI makeover, not sure there is a purpose for me to keep using the Tapatalk app. I mean sure, it can let me access some obscure forums, but XDA? That is the 75% of business.

I have unistalled. After 50 days since last update no solution provide fortin forum XDA crash. Disappointed because manyoke me and not solved. Samsung Galaxy S20 ultra 5g. Update 1st Jan 21: I believe it is unfair that a paid app does not take in consideration so many complains after latest update (8th Nov 2020) regarding forums not anymore available and after almost two months has done nothing to solve and not even replied. Not professional

Is this version being trashed to force people to sign up for ad-free VIP status with the other app in the store? I just got an email telling me about this great "deal"on getting discounts for ad-free service, but I thought I already had that with this version of the app. What's going on?

Clunky, "updates" break my sign ins 100% of the time. Even though I am a licensed subscriber, if I click on a link to a group (outside of Tapatalk) the app forces itself open as the only way to read the group and most of the time it does a quick open/close of Tapatalk making it impossible to read my choice of articles. Just bad.
Xda does not work.
Update: Didn't think it could suck anymore but latest update completely breaks ability to upload photos. Great job!
I paid for this before why should I pay again?????? 😡😡😡😡😡🤬🤬🤬🤬
Awful experience. Can't load almost anything properly. Please do something.
Very buggy.
No longer works. Since last update I cannot even view my subscriptions or forums I belong to. When I open the app, it just spins. Worthless.

I just realized thelat Tapatalk doesn't update the pro version. This leave people who bought it formerly no choice but to get free version and upgrade. I would appreciate if dev updates this pro version.
App is totally screwed up after last update. Can't even find the forums I used to follow. Absolutely waste of space now.

Recent performance is terrible. Cannot connect to entire first.such as XDA. Have to exit and reload in order to load an area. Cleared cache, data, reinstalled. Error messages popping up. Disappointed and will most likely cancel subscription soon.

The developers are consistent with breaking the app with updates like they have done with nearly every update in the last 10 years or so. Edit 2.10.18: Installed older version that at least somewhat works. Edit 11.9.20: Still using old version 8.2.0 from several years ago and will NEVER update this app again, based on dozens of reviews saying nothing has changed AND the fact the developers are charging AGAIN for an app that's already been paid for. It was also pulled from Play Store for weeks.
Works well for me.
What is the difference between this one and the other one with monthly subscription? 🤔
Used to be good. No longer works with most forums.
Nothing works anymore, seems like it is now abandoned and they just want more money for the subscription version.

New phone and again, nothing loads. I get my main screen, but any thread I click on just sits at the spinning circle/loading screen. Very annoying to have to open up on the web which defeats the purpose of having the app.

Have been using Tapatalk for a very long time and just in the past couple of days I had an issue with the forums not loading. I sent a message to Support and within 15 minutes the problem was solved. Can't beat that for support! Thanks!
Link's to tapatalk pro fail to load. App has, 10.3.20, stopped loading altogether.
Not working properly can't access forums. Get with it people!
Seems XDA will be changing their Forums and they advise that Tapatalk will no longer work. Oh well, I guess I'll be removing this app when that happens.
Sad that now they want to charge every month... Edit: all good now, my go to for XDA and other forums

Please modify this app to allow for storage of cache on the SD card of Samsung phones. I have to keep clearing the cache as it kills my phone by using up to about 2 Gb of cache. Please consider this change request. Seriously, no reply from the developers. Great support guys lol
Fails to open pages the vast majority of the time. You click a link, see the Tapatalk logo and then it closes and returns you to the original page.
Slow loading or not loading at all, broken attachment previews and unable to download them...

Update: this app seems to be getting worse. Parts of the app just don't load sometimes and I have to force stop it and start again. I'm almost ready to give it 2 stars. to love tapatalk but now it seems to be more buggy. One example is deep links from notifications used to work and now they don't. So when I tap on a notification that interests me I just have to watch a spinner spinning and then go and find the topic myself. Hopefully one day it returns to its former glory.
notifications dont work anymore! Tapatalk is pushing us to the bloated version.
Doesn't load sure anymore.
Use it heaps across multiple devices. Just keeps getting better.

New updates keep you from disabling specific notifications and instead forced you to disable all notifications in the Android settings. This essentially let's the app spam you with notifications you don't care about. Just download your forums specific app instead.

USMESSAGEBOARD Forum does not work on TAPATALK PRO. It's been like this for several months! Where did this forum go? They need to update their Plug-in. The app has its ups and downs. It should implement a maintenance schedule to iron out some of its problems. It could be better.
Still the best Forum manager. Love it.
Uninstalled the app. I find it easier to read the forums in browser. Biggest issue is that when I read a long thread, the app does not remember where I was if I leave the app and come back later.
youtube previews stopped working

So I purchased this and now I get spams for VIP access!! Why did I pay to get spammed for more money? What a bunch of scammers. Do not give them your money or use this worthless app. I am happy to pay for lack of ads or to support development effort but this is just robbery. Pay for the full version, and then have to pay again not to have ads - what a rip off! I have a few choice words for how I feel, but they are not for polite company.
Latest update is sending random notifications for random threads on random forums I follow. I have all notifications disabled other than PM and Quote. Nice work dev.....
Painful!
The app is now logging me out of AVSforum at least once per day. I'm having to login to like, bookmark, or reply to posts daily. Previously was logged in for months if not years at a time.
I have constant login challenges where i get logged out and then it says i have to reconfirm my email address, but then no email is sent. Great product, bad experience!
Gone down hill, threads dont load have to union stall and reinstall. Too bad we have to pay for things that dont work.

Had Tapatalk Pro for a long time. It stopped loading threads recently. Also didn't keep track of replies very well. After a while, it also quit uploading photos. Had to revert back to the free Tapatalk app which is also irritating due to ads, but at least it works.
Stopped loading threads. Logo just spins. Useless
Slow... So slow
Forums aren't loading anymore. Just keeps trying to load but nothing happens.

Works randomly recently... Stopped loading threads a few days ago, can only view threads in Web link now. Been using this for a few years now, going to look for alternatives now. For a paid app I'm very disappointed
Can no longer upload a picture. Tried with several forums, and several different pics (including some I've uploaded in the past). Broken.
Update the app already..Regular AD filled Tapa get updated all the time. I have a VIP Account so no ads show but this Pro version needs updating as well
It's behaving realy bad lately. Searches and my subscriptions shows errors or just black screen. Stay away

Has a wide variety of forums covered - app support is good as I used to have issues with speed but that's since been addressed. The new interface and logo is appreciated, and is much more astetically appealing when displaying the shortcut on my home screen. All around great update. Edit: Updated review to reflect the break of promise on the consumer side. Purchased for lifetime VIP benefits not for that to be breached and be charged for month to month.

Worked great for a good while, then would keep repeating the same posts over and over even after I had read them. Contacted the team and they supposedly couldn't figure out what I was talking about and got nowhere with any of the problems, its about right after you have paid for something, sucks
Don't know why you're all moaning about it. Works good. Still works good. Absolutely fine. Thanks Devs 🙂
Please add a push notification toggle option so I can disable these trending stories notifications I don't care for. Otherwise I will just have to disable notifications entirely for the app.

I'm not sure how correct is this info. But BBS app reports com.quoord.tapatalkHD.TapatalkPro as an app that is using 100% of the time the following 2 sensors: accelerometer and gyroscope. Do you know something about it? I can provide screenshot

excellent progress so far. Unable to see or post to ones personal gallery. This APP has been refined many times, for better or worse, cheers to DEV('s) for non-stop commitment. Paid version is the way to go, still ads but not nearly like the freebie. Of all the things, i dont get why some fourums are still off limits? (rctech) I know the OWNER loses money when they allow taptalk IN, but its also much more traffic. (ad revenue) could we have future considerations that would allow us such?
Pro is no longer pro for life. Works 30% of the time decently. The other 70% it's just frozen. Greed by dev is taking its toll.

Was working fine till I just ran the latest update and now I can't access my forum. This is not acceptable for a paid app. ETA: it wouldn't auto login. Once I clicked no, I wasn't screen name, then it let me enter my password and it logged me in. It's working but that is a terrible flow.
Huge steps backwards

"forum home screen is totally rewritten..." stop making radical rewrites of important functionality and ruining them! Just bring back the ability for me to order them the way I WANT THEM not two worthless options I don't want! LOL at latest change log: *many bug fixes* - guess there were *many* bugs and likely still are. 😂

Slow af, image quality is suddenly insanely low, no attachment option, only upload and link to tapatalks storage which is concerning as they could pull the plug or do a Photobucket and blackmail you, which would break millions of threads of forums with images suddenly vanishing. The whole reason users such as myself have bought this app was specifically so there would be no ads and no subscriptions of any kind. If they want to make more money, then they should leave the ads in the free version of the app, not punish old customers that already paid. Offering a 6 month VIP subscription is a joke.

While setting up the app, first I noticed an app dialogue in very bad English: "what's interest you?" Sorry to say, you can't do that. 15 years ago cheap routers made in China had user interfaces with crappy English. The really major issue with Tapatalk, though, is that in my portfolio of "groups" I cannot actually group the groups, e. g. by subject or by language. All the app offers is switching between a list view of groups you're subscribed to and a tile view, and you can sort them by alphabet, by most visited or by last visited. This is totally insufficient. The more groups you subscribe to, the higher the level of organisation in the group section you'll want/need. On the other hand, Tapatalk is Tapatalk and there's no alternative to it.

replyContent: Forums being lost, especially if you have a Tapatalk ID account is an issue we have not come across so we would greatly appreciate any details to help us improve. Passwords however are not something we store on our servers for security. So if any cache or cleaner app was used to somehow clear it locally, you will have to enter them again.

Google clearly states that tablet and phone apps should be published to Google Play as ONE apk/app. This is silly having a separate app just for tablets. What Tapatalk should have done is updated the phone app to ICS design standards, and added multi-pane UI elements that are enabled when used on a tablet. This is the proper way to make an Android app, and is how the Gmail, Chrome, Currents, Evernote, DriverDiary, etc. apps are done. Android on a phone and Android on a tablet is not a different OS! There is no reason for there to be separate apps for each. Android has all the necessary tools in place for tablet UI and phone UI in the same app!
